  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://cdn.inghams.co.uk/ImageGen.ashx?image=/media/7247245/northern-lights-2.jpg" alt="Polar Express Adventure Checklist" /></p>
<ul>
<li>Warm clothing and layers – temperatures in Narvik average at approx. - 2° at this time of year, but can be varied, so it is important to have the right clothes to be as comfortable as possible during your trip, so we recommend thermals and winter jacket/salopettes if you have them. Layers are best as you will be going indoors to outdoors on some of the activities.<br /><br /></li>
<li>Guests on the Polar Express Adventure who wish to spend an afternoon skiing will need to bring their own ski clothing and goggles as this is not available locally.<br /><br /></li>
<li>Warm, sturdy footwear - there may be snow and ice on the ground at times, so make sure you bring sturdy comfortable and ideally waterproof shoes. If you feel more comfortable with crampons, please feel free to bring them although many places will request you remove them before venturing inside.<br /><br /></li>
<li>Camera and tripod – essential for capturing great photos of the Northern Lights! Our guides on your Northern Lights Safari will be ready with tips<br /><br /></li>
<li>Driving License – if you wish to take part in Snowmobiling at Abisko (Polar Express Adventure only), please see below. Extra excursions in Sweden are payable locally by card, or to the Inghams Rep in Norwegian Krona to save you taking out Swedish currency.<br /><br /></li>
</ul>
